SESSION PLAN
-It is a simply stated flexible and individualized teacher aid for a conducting a session or module
-It is based on the curriculum of the unit of competency

Different Types of Training Delivery Modes
-Individualy Study (Modular/self-paced learning)
  >a competency-based training modality where the trainee is allowed to progress at his own pace
-Dualized Mode TRaining Delivery
  >programs would comprise oth, in-school and in-industry trainings or fieldwork components
-Supervised-Industry TRaining or On-the-Job training
  >enhances the knowledge and skills of the trainees through actual experience in the workplace
-Distance Learning
  >Trainees use resource packages to learn off campus

Training Methods
-Lecure/Discussion
-Group Discussion
-Individual Study / Self-Paced
-Demonstration
-Role Playing
-Audio-Visual Presentation
-Field Trip

Benefits of a Session Plan
-It gives the trainers an idea ofwhere they are and where they are going
-It gives the trainers a clear idea of what they are doing
-Gives a trainers a firm base to review their performance
-Give the trainers a starting point if they have to do the training again with another learner or group of learners

Components of Session Plan
-Industry Sector
-Qualification Title and Level
-Unit of Competency
-Module Title
-Learning Outcomes
-Introduction
-Learning Activities
-Evaluation/Assessment Plan
-Teacher's Self-Reflection

